-- U.S. top court takes up key housing discrimination case
-- By Lawrence Hurley
-- Thu Oct 02, 2014 09:39AM EDT
-- None



WASHINGTON, Oct 2 (Reuters) - The U.S. Supreme Court on Thursday agreed to weigh whether the state of Texas violated a fair housing law by disproportionately awarding low-income housing tax credits to developers who own properties in poor, minority-dominated neighborhoods.

